-- Tottenham Defender Walker Signs Contract Extension Through 2017
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-03T13:58:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/tottenham-defender-walker-signs-contract-extension-through-2017.html
Tottenham Hotspur defender  Kyle Walker 
signed a contract extension through 2017, the Premier League
club said on its website.  Walker, 21, took over as Tottenham’s starting right back
this season after loan spells at Queens Park Rangers and  Aston
Villa  in 2010-11. He was named the Young Player of the Year by
the Professional Footballer’s Association last month and was
selected to the group’s team of the year.  Walker also made his debut for the England national team in
November in games against world champion Spain and Sweden.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  